reserve S for RealNormSpace;
reserve T for RealNormSpace;
reserve f for (PartFunc of S,T);
reserve x0 for (Point of S);
reserve x1 for (Point of S);
reserve x2 for (Point of S);
theorem
(((f is  total & (for x1 holds (for x2 holds ( f /. ( x1 + x2 ) ) = ( ( f /. x1 ) + ( f /. x2 ) )))) & (ex x0 st f is_continuous_in x0)) implies f is_continuous_on (the carrier of S))
proof
assume that
A1: f is  total
and
A2: (for x1 holds (for x2 holds ( f /. ( x1 + x2 ) ) = ( ( f /. x1 ) + ( f /. x2 ) )));
A3: ( dom f ) = (the carrier of S) by A1,PARTFUN1:def 2;
given x0 such that
A4: f is_continuous_in x0;

( ( f /. x0 ) + ( 0. T ) ) = ( f /. x0 ) by RLVECT_1:4
.= ( f /. ( x0 + ( 0. S ) ) ) by RLVECT_1:4
.= ( ( f /. x0 ) + ( f /. ( 0. S ) ) ) by A2;
then A5: ( f /. ( 0. S ) ) = ( 0. T ) by RLVECT_1:8;
A6:now
let x1;
( 0. T ) = ( f /. ( x1 + ( - x1 ) ) ) by A5,RLVECT_1:5
.= ( ( f /. x1 ) + ( f /. ( - x1 ) ) ) by A2;
hence ( - ( f /. x1 ) ) = ( f /. ( - x1 ) ) by RLVECT_1:6;
end;
A7:now
let x1;
let x2;
thus ( f /. ( x1 - x2 ) ) = ( ( f /. x1 ) + ( f /. ( - x2 ) ) ) by A2
.= ( ( f /. x1 ) - ( f /. x2 ) ) by A6;
end;
now
let x1;
let r being Real;
assume that
x1 in (the carrier of S)
and
A8: r > ( 0 );
set y = ( x1 - x0 );
consider s such that A9: ( 0 ) < s and A10: (for x1 holds ((x1 in ( dom f ) & ||. ( x1 - x0 ) .|| < s) implies ||. ( ( f /. x1 ) - ( f /. x0 ) ) .|| < r)) by A4,A8,CKB13:1;
take s;
thus s > ( 0 ) by A9;
let x2;
assume that
x2 in (the carrier of S)
and
A11: ||. ( x2 - x1 ) .|| < s;
A12: ( y + x0 ) = ( x1 - ( x0 - x0 ) ) by RLVECT_1:29
.= ( x1 - ( 0. S ) ) by RLVECT_1:15
.= x1 by RLVECT_1:13;
then A13: ||. ( ( x2 - y ) - x0 ) .|| = ||. ( x2 - x1 ) .|| by RLVECT_1:27;
||. ( ( f /. x2 ) - ( f /. x1 ) ) .|| = ||. ( ( f /. x2 ) - ( ( f /. y ) + ( f /. x0 ) ) ) .|| by A2,A12
.= ||. ( ( ( f /. x2 ) - ( f /. y ) ) - ( f /. x0 ) ) .|| by RLVECT_1:27
.= ||. ( ( f /. ( x2 - y ) ) - ( f /. x0 ) ) .|| by A7;
hence ||. ( ( f /. x2 ) - ( f /. x1 ) ) .|| < r by A3,A10,A11,A13;
end;
hence thesis by A3,CKB27:1;
end;
